events.name: Auburn Tigers at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Cam Newton passed for a career-best 335 yards and four touchdowns, plus ran for a couple of TDs to lead No. 2 Auburn past 18th-ranked South Carolina 56-17 for the Southeastern Conference title Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Newton lifts Auburn to title game

events.name: Oregon Ducks at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.description: No. 1 Oregon has wrapped up a spot in the BCS national title game for the first time in school history, beating Oregon State 37-20 in the Civil War rivalry on Saturday.

Travis Lewis had an interception in the end zone and recovered two fumbles as No. 10 Oklahoma rallied from a 17-point deficit to beat Nebraska 23-20 on Saturday night in the Big 12 championship, the Cornhuskers' last game in the conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: OU clips Nebraska to take Big 12 title

events.name: Utah State Aggies at Boise State Broncos

headlines.description: Kellen Moore threw three touchdown passes, ran for another and No. 9 Boise State bounced back from a loss that ended its BCS hopes, beating Utah State 50-14 Saturday in its Western Athletic Conference farewell.

events.name: Florida State Seminoles at Virginia Tech Hokies

headlines.description: Tyrod Taylor threw three touchdown passes and scrambled for another and surging Virginia Tech captured its third Atlantic Coast Conference title in four years with a 44-33 victory over Florida State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Va. Tech handles FSU for ACC crown

events.name: Nevada Wolf Pack at Louisiana Tech Bulldogs

headlines.description: Colin Kaepernick tied an NCAA record for touchdowns rushing by a quarterback and Nevada won a share of the Western Athletic Conference title with a 35-17 victory over Louisiana Tech on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kaepernick, Nevada cruise to snag WAC share

events.name: Rutgers Scarlet Knights at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Geno Smith threw for a career-high 352 yards, Ryan Clarke had three short touchdown runs and No. 23 West Virginia overcame turnover problems to beat Rutgers 35-14 on Saturday and clinch at least a share of the Big East title.
headlines.shortLinkText: WVU rolls to grab share of Big East

events.name: Western Illinois Leathernecks at Appalachian State Mountaineers

notes.headline: NCAA DIVISION I FOOTBALL CHAMPIONSHIP - SECOND ROUND
CONFERENCE USA CHAMPIONSHIP GAME - PRESENTED BY HOTELPLANNER.com

headlines.description: Latavius Murray rushed for 94 yards and scored two touchdowns Saturday to lead Central Florida to a 17-7 victory over Southern Methodist in the Conference USA championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray's 2 TDs lift UCF to C-USA title

headlines.description: CINCINNATI -- Dion Lewis ran for a career-high 261 yards and four touchdowns on a snow-covered field Saturday, leading Pittsburgh to a 28-10 victory over Cincinnati and at least a share of the Big East title.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pitt rumbles past Cincinnati for share of Big East

events.name: Georgia Southern Eagles at William & Mary Tribe

venue.fullName: Walter J. Zable Stadium at Cary Field

notes.headline: NCAA DIVISION I FOOTBALL CHAMPIONSHIP - SECOND ROUND

events.name: Troy Trojans at Florida Atlantic Owls
San Jose State Spartans at Idaho Vandals
Middle Tennessee Blue Raiders at Florida Intl Golden Panthers
Washington Huskies at Washington State Cougars

headlines.description: Jake Locker and Washington became bowl eligible for the first time in eight years with a 35-28 win over rival Washington State in the 103rd Apple Cup on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Locker, Washington win Apple Cup for bowl bid

events.name: Connecticut Huskies at South Florida Bulls

headlines.description: Dave Teggart had four field goals, including a career-long 52-yarder with 17 seconds to play, as Connecticut clinched the Big East's automatic Bowl Championship Series berth Saturday night with a 19-16 win over South Florida.
headlines.shortLinkText: UConn nabs first BCS bid with late FG

headlines.description: Southern California wrapped up its first season under NCAA sanctions with a 28-14 victory over UCLA on Saturday night.

events.name: UNLV Rebels at Hawai'i Rainbow Warriors

headlines.description: Bryant Moniz threw for 380 yards and four touchdowns and ran for two more scores to help No. 25 Hawaii rout UNLV 59-21 on Saturday night, giving the Warriors their sixth 10-win season in school history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawaii romps over UNLV to earn 10-win season
